The paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks in the context of image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the interpretation of network decisions, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of gradient-based methods, which are commonly used in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the accuracy of interpretation algorithms, which is related to the performance evaluation of neural networks (cs.NE).
